            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1326834037,
            "creation_date": 1326834037,
            "body": "<p>I would suggest using this simplified regex for your problem like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Matcher m = Pattern.compile(\"SLOT\\\\s+(\\\\d+).*?Board\\\\s+State\\\\s+is\\\\s+(\\\\w+)\",\n            Pattern.DOTALL).matcher(text);\nwhile(m.find())\n    System.out.printf(\"Slot is [%s], Board is [%s]%n\", m.group(1), m.group(2));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><strong>OUTPUT:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Slot is [2], Board is [Val]\nSlot is [3], Board is [Val2]\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 8901687,
            "question_id": 8901055
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/vSC6X.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1042420,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1048157,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1048157/milad-naseri",
                "reputation": 4128,
                "display_name": "Milad Naseri",
                "accept_rate": 88
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1326834209,
            "creation_date": 1326831383,
            "body": "<p>This should do the job:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String regex = \"(SLOT\\\\s*\\\\d+)\\\\s*\\\\([^\\\\)]+\\\\)\\\\s*:\\\\s*\\\\S*[\\n\\r](\\\\s*[^\\n\\r]+[\\n\\r])*(Board[^\\n\\r]*)\";\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Notice that I have used <code>[^\\n\\r]<\/code> instead of <code>.<\/code> in case you compile it using <code>DOTALL<\/code>. If not, you can as easily change every <code>[^\\n\\r]<\/code> to <code>.<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>If the <code>(something): something<\/code> part is not mandatory after the <code>SLOT \\d+<\/code> part, you can use thins one:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String regex = \"(SLOT\\\\s*\\\\d+)[^\\n\\r]*[\\n\\r](\\\\s*[^\\n\\r]+[\\n\\r])*(Board[^\\n\\r]*)\";\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 8901134,
            "question_id": 8901055,
            "last_edit_date": 1326834209
        }
